-- CAC 40 Index Declines; BNP, Societe Generale, CGG-Veritas, Securidev Move
-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 2010-09-23T16:12:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/french-stocks-drop-cgg-veritas-falls-for-third-day-while-faurecia-gains.html
France’s  CAC 40 Index  dropped 0.7
percent to 3,710.61 at the 5:30 p.m. close in Paris, the
measure’s third consecutive decline. The  SBF 120 Index  also lost
0.7 percent.  The following shares were among the most active in the
French equity market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses
after company names.  BNP Paribas SA  (BNP FP) and  Societe Generale SA  (GLE FP),
France’s biggest banks, lost 2.5 percent to 53.90 euros and 1.7
percent to 43.51 euros, respectively. Europe’s Stoxx 600 Banks
Index tumbled as much as 2 percent today.  Cie. Generale de Geophysique-Veritas  (GA FP), which trades
as CGG-Veritas, sank 3.9 percent to 15.91 euros, the biggest
drop in more than a month. The provider of geophysical services
was downgraded to “neutral” from “overweight” at JPMorgan
Chase & Co.  Securidev SA  (SCDV FP) surged 6.1 percent to 22.50 euros,
the stock’s highest price in two years. The maker of
conventional and electronic locks returned to profit in the
first half of the year with net income of 4.3 million euros
($5.74 million). It maintained its full-year forecast.  Thermocompact SA  (THER FP) rose 2 percent to 13.98 euros,
an eleventh day of gains and the longest winning streak since
the shares went on sale to the public in 1998. The supplier of
cable coatings for the electronics industry posted a 2.36
million-euro first-half profit, up from an 883,000-euro loss
last year.  Vet’Affaires  (VET FP) jumped 5 percent to 24.15 euros, the
highest price since January 2008. The French discount-clothing
retailer returned to profit in the first half and forecast full-
year revenue of more than 100 million euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Julie Cruz  in Frankfurt at 
 jcruz6@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at   dmerritt1@bloomberg.net . 